                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>6</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="71128" author="yujian" created="Fri, 8 Nov 2013 16:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4219&quot; title=&quot;posix test_1: fpathconf.8 and pathconf.10 failed: did not return the value of NAME_MAX&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4219&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4219&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; can fix this issue. So, the ticket is closed as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4219&quot; title=&quot;posix test_1: fpathconf.8 and pathconf.10 failed: did not return the value of NAME_MAX&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4219&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4219&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="70734" author="yujian" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2013 16:28:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre build: &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_4/49/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_4/49/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
FSTYPE=zfs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;posix test results:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e74b645e-4634-11e3-810a-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e74b645e-4634-11e3-810a-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="69538" author="adilger" created="Tue, 22 Oct 2013 17:08:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like ZFS* is somehow reporting that NAME_MAX IS 256 but it only accepts filenames of 255 bytes.  This confuses POSIX. Probably the easiest thing is to change osd-zfs to return a max filename size of 255 to match ldiskfs. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;*&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; pathconf() results might be generated inside glibc instead of the filesystem, which is annoying and needs a patch to glibc to fix. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="69532" author="sarah" created="Tue, 22 Oct 2013 16:51:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hit this error in lustre-b2_5 zfs testing&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a25115d8-3509-11e3-b76d-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a25115d8-3509-11e3-b76d-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
